text = "Nobody plays with dumb toys anymore. All the toys will need to
be programmed with software. Even the simplest ones. Press
the GLYPH BUTTONS to insert CODE GLYPHS into the program.
You need the right pattern of glyphs to successfully code your toy.

Check the compiler error after you complete the code. RED GLYPHS
are the wrong type. PURPLE GLYPHS are the correct type but in
the wrong spot. BLUE GLYPHS are the correct type in the correct spot.
Knowing how to read the compiler errors is key to successful programming."
